caption.p: Dose-dependent transduction rates of SARS-CoV-2 pseudoviruses. Generated SARS-CoV-2 pseudoviruses were serially diluted and then transduced into Vero-E6 cells. Transduction rate of SARS-CoV-2 was gradually reduced in a dose-dependent manner. According to the transduction rate curve, the titer of SARS-CoV-2 pseudovirus was quantified as 2.36 × 10 6 transduction unit.
